.TH diameter_codec 3 "diameter 2.6.1" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
diameter_codec \- Decode and encode of Diameter messages.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Incoming Diameter messages are decoded from binary() before being communicated to \fIdiameter_app\fR callbacks. Similarly, outgoing Diameter messages are encoded into binary() before being passed to the appropriate \fIdiameter_transport\fR module for transmission. The functions documented here implement the default encode/decode.

.PP
\fBWARNING: \fRThe diameter user does not need to call functions here explicitly when sending and receiving messages using \fIdiameter:call/4\fR and the callback interface documented in \fIdiameter_app\fR: diameter itself provides encode/decode as a consequence of configuration passed to \fIdiameter:start_service/2\fR, and the results may differ from those returned by the functions documented here, depending on configuration.


.PP
The header() and packet() records below are defined in diameter.hrl, which can be included as follows.

.IP
.nf
-include_lib("diameter/include/diameter.hrl").

.fi

.PP
Application-specific records are defined in the hrl files resulting from dictionary file compilation.

.SS "DATA TYPES"


.sp
